1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,369
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,371 --> 00:00:05,337
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,339 --> 00:00:07,373
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,375 --> 00:00:09,241
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:13,014 --> 00:00:15,514
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:17,249
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,251 --> 00:00:19,251
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:21,720
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,722 --> 00:00:24,223
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,225 --> 00:00:26,025
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:29,495
Hi, jimmy.

12
00:00:29,497 --> 00:00:32,031
Big jim:
<i>Rapture is your product, max.</i>

13
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,799
Which I never could've gotten
off the ground

14
00:00:33,801 --> 00:00:35,367
Without my
secret ingredient.

15
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:36,402
Liquid propane.
This town seems

16
00:00:36,404 --> 00:00:38,103
<i>To have a hell of a lot of it.</i>

17
00:00:38,105 --> 00:00:39,204
Duke knew about this?

18
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:40,372
He didn't want you to know.

19
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:42,708
Linda:
Duke?

20
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:44,109
What the hell were you up to?

21
00:00:44,111 --> 00:00:45,411
Max:
<i>The pillow talk between you</i>

22
00:00:45,413 --> 00:00:46,512
<i>And julia is gonna be</i>

23
00:00:46,514 --> 00:00:47,713
Done when
she finds out

24
00:00:47,715 --> 00:00:49,181
You murdered her husband.

25
00:00:49,183 --> 00:00:50,549
You're not bulletproof, max.
I have

26
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,251
An insurance policy in place.

27
00:00:52,253 --> 00:00:53,485
Anything bad
happens to me,

28
00:00:53,487 --> 00:00:54,686
Your secrets
still come out.

29
00:00:54,688 --> 00:00:56,422
angie.

30
00:00:56,424 --> 00:00:57,723
The pink stars are falling
in lines.

31
00:00:57,725 --> 00:00:59,091
Joe:
<i>Norrie and I have had</i>

32
00:00:59,093 --> 00:01:00,125
The exact same seizure.

33
00:01:00,127 --> 00:01:02,795
Stopped working
after joe and norrie touched

34
00:01:02,797 --> 00:01:04,296
The dome
the other day.

35
00:01:04,298 --> 00:01:06,165
I still don't trust
those two.

36
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,733
Guess I was
sleepwalking.

37
00:01:07,735 --> 00:01:10,202
But why did
I bring this thing here?

38
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:32,424
no sleepwalking.

39
00:01:32,426 --> 00:01:33,792
Good boy.

40
00:01:38,131 --> 00:01:39,598
what the...

41
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,200
Sorry.

42
00:01:41,202 --> 00:01:43,335
Joe, look
what's inside the mini-dome.

43
00:01:43,337 --> 00:01:44,603
Whoa.

44
00:01:44,605 --> 00:01:47,139
Angie: Will
you guys shut up?
Angie,

45
00:01:47,141 --> 00:01:48,807
The egg has a visitor.

46
00:01:54,447 --> 00:01:56,482
That's a caterpillar.

47
00:01:56,484 --> 00:01:58,784
But it wasn't there
last night.

48
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:00,686
Maybe it was under the dirt.

49
00:02:00,688 --> 00:02:03,288
Trapped inside
like the big dome trapped us.

50
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:06,325
Joe:
Wherever it came from,
it was no accident.

51
00:02:06,327 --> 00:02:08,694
Look at those black and
white and yellow stripes.

52
00:02:08,696 --> 00:02:09,695
Yeah?

53
00:02:09,697 --> 00:02:11,430
And?

54
00:02:11,432 --> 00:02:14,299
It's a caterpillar that will
turn into a monarch butterfly.

55
00:02:15,268 --> 00:02:17,402
"the monarch will be crowned."

56
00:02:17,404 --> 00:02:19,404
Julia
heard that

57
00:02:19,406 --> 00:02:21,306
When she touched this thing
out in the woods.

58
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,841
Joe: Maybe she'll know
what this means.
No, we all agreed

59
00:02:22,843 --> 00:02:24,877
Not to tell her that we have it.
Yeah, but
she might be

60
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:27,880
The fourth handprint
this mini-dome needs to do...

61
00:02:27,882 --> 00:02:29,448
Whatever it's gonna do.

62
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:33,218
Like... Turn off the dome.

63
00:02:34,621 --> 00:02:37,456
Okay, but julia
hasn't had seizures.

64
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:40,325
yeah.

65
00:02:40,327 --> 00:02:41,660
Okay.

66
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:06,652
We still have to find whoever
the fourth handprint belongs to.

67
00:03:06,654 --> 00:03:08,520
Someone with seizures.

68
00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:11,657
we should find others
who've had them.

69
00:03:11,659 --> 00:03:14,459
Angie:
Good. Let's cover
the mini-dome.

70
00:03:37,817 --> 00:03:40,886
♪

71
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:57,769
Hello, barbie. You're up early.

72
00:03:57,771 --> 00:04:00,572
We need to talk about max.

73
00:04:01,874 --> 00:04:05,277
Sounds like someone's not
too happy to see her yesterday.

74
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:07,813
And you were?

75
00:04:07,815 --> 00:04:11,683
Woman's a...
Piece of work, isn't she?

76
00:04:11,685 --> 00:04:15,554
more than I knew.

77
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:17,689
Care to, uh...

78
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:21,526
Share exactly how it is you two
are in business together?

79
00:04:21,528 --> 00:04:22,661
Sure.

80
00:04:22,663 --> 00:04:24,496
Right after you do.

81
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:27,432
Well, then,

82
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:28,967
Enemy of my enemy,
what are we gonna do?

83
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:31,903
We can't really move against her
with the dirt she says she has

84
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:33,538
On the both of us.
Unless...

85
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:37,476
We get rid of whatever
this insurance policy is.

86
00:04:37,478 --> 00:04:38,877
But where would that be?

87
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,712
Well, she says
she's staying at a house

88
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:42,648
Whose owners got trapped
outside the dome.

89
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:44,916
No. No, she's too smart
for that.

90
00:04:44,918 --> 00:04:48,453
You know, she's got this, uh,
legitimate real estate company.

91
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,290
The... Osiris corporation.

92
00:04:51,292 --> 00:04:54,693
Buys homes mostly in westlake,
but I know she's got a few here.

93
00:04:54,695 --> 00:04:56,428
That's worth a look.
Yeah.

94
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:57,763
You know which houses are hers?

95
00:04:57,765 --> 00:04:59,765
The town clerk's office
got record. I'll, uh...

96
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:05,837
You mean, so you can...
You can bury your secrets

97
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:08,840
And leave mine out there in
the open for the world to see.

98
00:05:08,842 --> 00:05:10,575
You think I'd screw you over?

99
00:05:10,577 --> 00:05:12,678
You're a used car salesman, jim.

100
00:05:18,518 --> 00:05:20,585
Sure. We'll go together.

101
00:05:28,928 --> 00:05:31,463
Yeah, I'm seeing at least
a dozen houses here

102
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:33,532
That were purchased
by the osiris corporation.

103
00:05:33,534 --> 00:05:36,001
Most of those max remodeled
and flipped 'em within a year

104
00:05:36,003 --> 00:05:38,837
But, uh... Not this one.

105
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:42,641
Bought it in 2005.
Never put back on the market.

106
00:05:42,643 --> 00:05:44,409
It's on bird island?

107
00:05:44,411 --> 00:05:47,045
Yeah. It's in the middle
of lake eastpointe

108
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:49,715
But still under the dome.
Only a few vacation homes

109
00:05:49,717 --> 00:05:51,883
Out there. Not a bad place
to hide whatever it is

110
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:54,720
She says she's got on us.

111
00:05:54,722 --> 00:05:56,121
Probably shouldn't go unarmed.

112
00:05:56,123 --> 00:05:58,924
You don't think I'd let max
have all the guns, do you?

113
00:05:58,926 --> 00:06:01,393
Max:
Uh-oh. What are
you two doing?

114
00:06:01,395 --> 00:06:04,463
No, just some
town business.

115
00:06:04,465 --> 00:06:06,665
You know, there are things
going on here that don't

116
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,667
Involve you.
Mm, for now anyway.

117
00:06:08,669 --> 00:06:09,735
Here you go.

118
00:06:11,605 --> 00:06:13,105
"espresso"?

119
00:06:13,107 --> 00:06:15,040
"dark chocolate,
silk-infused conditioner"?

120
00:06:15,042 --> 00:06:16,908
I like my luxuries.

121
00:06:16,910 --> 00:06:18,777
Just because this damn dome
came down doesn't mean

122
00:06:18,779 --> 00:06:20,579
I'm gonna do without.

123
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:24,116
Some of that stuff.
No, I'm not... I'm not
doing your shopping.

124
00:06:24,118 --> 00:06:25,717
No. Just jimmy.

125
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:27,853
You and I have other business
to attend to.

126
00:06:29,689 --> 00:06:30,922
Max:
Or if you want,

127
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:32,457
I can reveal
all your dirty laundry

128
00:06:32,459 --> 00:06:33,825
And then we can see
how that goes.

129
00:06:38,598 --> 00:06:40,599
Barbie,
let's go.

130
00:07:14,734 --> 00:07:17,102
What the hell was that?
It sounded like thunder.

131
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:18,870
Dodee...

132
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:43,995
joe:
Dodee?

133
00:07:43,997 --> 00:07:45,130
Are you all right?

134
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:46,531
Where am I?

135
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:48,200
We're at the clinic.
We brought you here.

136
00:07:48,202 --> 00:07:50,135
Well, what happened to me?

137
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:51,670
You don't remember?

138
00:07:51,672 --> 00:07:54,239
- I remember...
- electricity.

139
00:07:54,241 --> 00:07:57,909
Was it... Was it the generator
outside the radio station?

140
00:07:59,111 --> 00:08:00,879
Yeah, that's right.

141
00:08:00,881 --> 00:08:02,614
We found you by your generator
outside the radio station.

142
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:04,749
We were passing by
and we heard a noise.

143
00:08:04,751 --> 00:08:06,184
And then we found you
with that burn on your hand.

144
00:08:06,186 --> 00:08:08,186
Yeah. Yeah,
I-I guess

145
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:10,689
Was, was being there.
Nurse adams:
Dodee.

146
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:12,190
What... Happened to her?

147
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:13,692
We think she got zapped
by a generator.

148
00:08:13,694 --> 00:08:15,160
Did she lose consciousness?

149
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:16,628
For, like, 20 minutes.

150
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:19,865
All right, well, thanks
for bringing her in.

151
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:21,266
I'll take good care of her.

152
00:08:23,636 --> 00:08:25,504
Nurse adams.

153
00:08:25,506 --> 00:08:27,506
Do you know anyone else
who's had seizures lately?

154
00:08:27,508 --> 00:08:28,673
Besides joe and I.

155
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:33,178
Not since your tenth grade
dance, angie.

156
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:35,714
What does that mean?

157
00:08:35,716 --> 00:08:37,716
What's wrong?

158
00:08:37,718 --> 00:08:39,918
Angie!

159
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:42,954
Hello?

160
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:46,291
Anyone here?

161
00:08:50,563 --> 00:08:52,230
hello?

162
00:08:52,232 --> 00:08:54,900
Hello?

163
00:08:54,902 --> 00:08:56,735
Linda.
Hey.

164
00:08:56,737 --> 00:09:00,171
Uh, I'm just looking
for barbie. Is he around?

165
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,908
I haven't seen him.

166
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:05,243
What's going on?

167
00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:08,280
A while back, you spoke
with andrea grinnell

168
00:09:08,282 --> 00:09:10,115
About some weird stuff
going on

169
00:09:10,117 --> 00:09:12,083
At the propane
warehouse, right?

170
00:09:12,085 --> 00:09:13,218
Yeah.

171
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,186
Did you ever follow up on it?

172
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:17,556
Honestly I thought
she was kind of loopy.

173
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:20,292
And then everything went to hell
and I just forgot about it.

174
00:09:20,294 --> 00:09:22,561
Why?

175
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,830
Andrea wasn't so loopy
after all.

176
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,633
Look at this.

177
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,275
I don't know who
this woman is.

178
00:09:37,277 --> 00:09:39,277
Here comes

179
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:41,313
Duke.

180
00:09:45,651 --> 00:09:47,686
She's handing him
money.

181
00:09:47,688 --> 00:09:49,220
All of which has something
to do with...

182
00:09:49,222 --> 00:09:52,290
A drug being made
using propane called rapture.

183
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:54,759
You think duke
was involved with drugs?

184
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:57,262
Reverend coggins,
too.

185
00:09:57,264 --> 00:10:00,765
I think coggins burned down
duke's house to hide evidence.

186
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:02,267
Now they're both dead, and...

187
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:03,802
I've driven myself crazy

188
00:10:03,804 --> 00:10:05,637
Searching this place
for an answer.

189
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:07,639
You knew duke better
than anyone.

190
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:09,307
Where else
would he stash something?

191
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:12,711
All he really cared
about was fly-fishing, bourbon,

192
00:10:12,713 --> 00:10:14,713
And that hat.

193
00:10:14,715 --> 00:10:17,015
The tackle box was
burned in the house,

194
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:19,184
He never left a
bottle unfinished

195
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:22,253
And he never took
that hat off his head.

196
00:10:36,268 --> 00:10:38,803
Well, hello there.

197
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:41,973
What do you unlock?

198
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:44,776
Safe-deposit box.

199
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:46,778
Bank of
chester's mill.

200
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:48,813
I'll drive.

201
00:11:09,735 --> 00:11:12,437
Yeah, you're not acting
suspicious.

202
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:23,248
Where you going so fast?

203
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,716
Nowhere.
Huh?

204
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:27,352
Ow!
Shut up before I add

205
00:11:27,354 --> 00:11:29,187
Damaging police property
to what you obviously

206
00:11:29,189 --> 00:11:32,991
Ripped off from someone.

207
00:11:32,993 --> 00:11:36,695
Salt?
So, I might've shoplifted it
from the convenience store.

208
00:11:36,697 --> 00:11:38,463
Yeah, but why steal that?
You kidding?

209
00:11:38,465 --> 00:11:41,733
Better than cash if you want
to get into the cement factory.

210
00:11:44,403 --> 00:11:46,471
Max:
Word of advice, barbie.

211
00:11:46,473 --> 00:11:50,341
Whatever you and big jim were
huddling about at town hall...

212
00:11:50,343 --> 00:11:51,710
Be careful.

213
00:11:51,712 --> 00:11:55,213
You mean kind of like
how I can trust you?

214
00:11:56,182 --> 00:11:58,450
I have never lied to you, dale.

215
00:11:58,452 --> 00:12:01,052
I'd like to think
the same about you.

216
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:08,026
So what's this business
we need to attend to?

217
00:12:08,028 --> 00:12:10,495
I'm guessing these people aren't
here for a church service.

218
00:12:10,497 --> 00:12:12,363
No, just a little
adult entertainment.

219
00:12:12,365 --> 00:12:15,100
It's been, what, nine days
since the dome came down?

220
00:12:15,102 --> 00:12:16,501
There's been no tv,
there's been no internet,

221
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:18,369
There's been
no fun at all.

222
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:20,505
Right, so now you smell
an opportunity

223
00:12:20,507 --> 00:12:23,975
For your usual booze,
cards, brothels.

224
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:25,310
Hey.

225
00:12:25,312 --> 00:12:27,912
I don't deal in
prostitution ever.

226
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:30,482
You got that?

227
00:12:30,484 --> 00:12:32,317
Come on.

228
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:59,811
Welcome
to my brave new world.

229
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:53,131
Who are you?

230
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,866
Sorry for the intrusion,
ma'am. I-I'm...

231
00:13:54,868 --> 00:13:57,836
Wait. Big jim rennie?

232
00:13:57,838 --> 00:13:59,838
From the car commercials?

233
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:02,307
♪ small price,
big savings. ♪

234
00:14:02,309 --> 00:14:04,209
That's me.
Well, then...

235
00:14:04,211 --> 00:14:07,045
It's hardly an intrusion.

236
00:14:07,047 --> 00:14:10,048
I like your ads.
You don't scream from the tv

237
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,250
Like the rest of 'em.
That's not my style, ma'am.

238
00:14:12,252 --> 00:14:13,585
Please, call me agatha.

239
00:14:13,587 --> 00:14:16,454
Agatha,
nice to meet you.

240
00:14:16,456 --> 00:14:18,022
This your house?
No.

241
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:19,490
I'm just the caretaker.

242
00:14:19,492 --> 00:14:21,626
Gardening and such.

243
00:14:21,628 --> 00:14:23,027
For, um...

244
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:24,529
For maxine seagrave?

245
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:26,331
Don't know a maxine.

246
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:28,399
The owner's oliver luckland.

247
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:31,502
He's on the other side of the
island, tending to his boat.

248
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:33,171
I came here
because,

249
00:14:33,173 --> 00:14:34,639
More important
than selling cars,

250
00:14:34,641 --> 00:14:36,641
I'm a councilman
for chester's mill,

251
00:14:36,643 --> 00:14:40,044
And I'm making my way around
to see if our citizens

252
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:41,613
Need anything
in this time of crisis.

253
00:14:41,615 --> 00:14:43,648
Yes, it is
shocking, isn't it?

254
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:46,985
I'm glad to be here
amid the peace and quiet.

255
00:14:46,987 --> 00:14:49,187
Is mr. Luckland gonna be long?

256
00:14:49,189 --> 00:14:51,356
Uh, c-can I wait for him?

257
00:14:51,358 --> 00:14:53,358
Inside?

258
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,093
We'll have a nice cup of tea.

259
00:14:55,095 --> 00:14:57,161
Great.

260
00:15:03,036 --> 00:15:04,636
Max:
What do you think
of my grand opening?

261
00:15:04,638 --> 00:15:07,438
I think it's a lot smaller
than you're used to, isn't it?

262
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:10,441
Oh, in time I'll have
the whole town here.

263
00:15:10,443 --> 00:15:12,176
How'd you put
all this together?

264
00:15:12,178 --> 00:15:15,113
By not sitting on my hands
for the past week.

265
00:15:15,115 --> 00:15:17,248
Some of these people
owed me from before.

266
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,250
I'm sure you'll recognize
a few familiar faces

267
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:20,351
From your collection duties.

268
00:15:20,353 --> 00:15:22,654
Say somebody needs eggs
for his family

269
00:15:22,656 --> 00:15:25,256
And he's got some spare
batteries. He comes in here,

270
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:27,191
Tries his luck.
If he wins, he trades up.

271
00:15:27,193 --> 00:15:29,594
If he loses... I win.

272
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:32,497
Uh...
people are already bartering

273
00:15:32,499 --> 00:15:34,032
Around town.
Yeah, that's for needs.

274
00:15:34,034 --> 00:15:35,533
In here, it's about vices.

275
00:15:35,535 --> 00:15:37,035
Come on.

276
00:15:37,037 --> 00:15:40,038
Everybody's got 'em. Even you.

277
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,373
You realize survival's at stake.

278
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:43,675
Yeah, mine.

279
00:15:43,677 --> 00:15:45,543
If I'm gonna be trapped
in this hellhole,

280
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:47,979
I am gonna live
as well as I can.

281
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:52,717
What's going on?

282
00:15:52,719 --> 00:15:54,585
I don't want to talk about it.

283
00:15:54,587 --> 00:15:57,455
Angie, come on,
you're obviously upset.

284
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:04,295
I think junior
is the fourth hand.

285
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:07,298
You're joking.
My tenth grade dance.

286
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:10,068
Junior got rushed to the clinic
for passing out.

287
00:16:10,070 --> 00:16:12,070
And everyone said it was
because he had been drinking,

288
00:16:12,072 --> 00:16:14,105
But nurse adams just said
someone had a seizure.

289
00:16:14,107 --> 00:16:15,139
But it can't be junior.

290
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:17,408
That guy
weirds me out.

291
00:16:17,410 --> 00:16:19,010
You think that I'm happy
about it?

292
00:16:19,012 --> 00:16:20,745
After what he did
to me?

293
00:16:20,747 --> 00:16:22,747
what does that mean?

294
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:33,124
You remember
how you couldn't find me

295
00:16:33,126 --> 00:16:34,459
After the dome came down?

296
00:16:34,461 --> 00:16:37,095
Wait.

297
00:16:37,097 --> 00:16:39,097
You were with him?

298
00:16:39,099 --> 00:16:41,099
He said he hadn't
even seen you.

299
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,101
Hmm.

300
00:16:43,103 --> 00:16:46,004
It wasn't... Voluntary.

301
00:16:46,006 --> 00:16:47,605
What?

302
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:50,008
He kept saying that the dome
was making me sick

303
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:51,676
And the only way
that I could

304
00:16:51,678 --> 00:16:53,444
Get better is
if I stayed with him.

305
00:16:53,446 --> 00:16:55,780
So he kidnapped you?
He had these reasons

306
00:16:55,782 --> 00:16:57,782
That seemed really
weird then, but...
Where is he?

307
00:16:57,784 --> 00:17:00,118
'cause I'm gonna kill him.
No, joe, if anyone's
gonna kill him,

308
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,252
It's gonna be me.
Not before I do.

309
00:17:01,254 --> 00:17:02,787
Get out of my way, angie!
Joe, stop!

310
00:17:02,789 --> 00:17:04,555
Stop it! Both of you,

311
00:17:04,557 --> 00:17:06,724
Stop!

312
00:17:06,726 --> 00:17:09,093
Look, I'm all
for kicking junior's ass

313
00:17:09,095 --> 00:17:10,495
If he kidnapped you,
ange.

314
00:17:10,497 --> 00:17:12,296
But if he's the fourth hand...

315
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,234
Yeah.
I guess

316
00:17:16,236 --> 00:17:18,569
You're right.

317
00:17:18,571 --> 00:17:23,107
Are you sure what junior had
way back then was a seizure?

318
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:25,109
Yeah.

319
00:17:25,111 --> 00:17:27,678
And that's not the only reason
I think it's him.

320
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,747
It's not?

321
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:33,785
I should show you something.

322
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:42,393
Looks like everyone left
the bank in a hurry

323
00:17:42,395 --> 00:17:43,694
After the dome came down.

324
00:17:43,696 --> 00:17:45,363
We could take
all the cash in here,

325
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:46,597
It wouldn't mean a thing.

326
00:17:46,599 --> 00:17:48,599
And to think it was money
that ruined

327
00:17:48,601 --> 00:17:52,236
My marriage and forced
my husband to run off.
Is that

328
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:53,571
Why peter left town?

329
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:55,840
After draining
our bank accounts

330
00:17:55,842 --> 00:17:57,842
And putting our home
in foreclosure

331
00:17:57,844 --> 00:17:59,510
To pay off his
gambling debts.

332
00:18:02,314 --> 00:18:05,783
I think deep down I knew
something was wrong.

333
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:08,719
I just didn't
want to see it.

334
00:18:16,161 --> 00:18:18,262
damn it.

335
00:18:19,231 --> 00:18:20,798
There must be
a key

336
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,867
To the safe-deposit room
around here somewhere.

337
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:29,540
Hey, maybe one of these...

338
00:18:33,847 --> 00:18:35,379
Got it!

339
00:18:45,390 --> 00:18:47,325
Oh, ho, ho, ho.

340
00:18:47,327 --> 00:18:48,860
Big junior rennie.

341
00:18:48,862 --> 00:18:50,461
Just junior.
Hmm.

342
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,130
What's going on inside?

343
00:18:52,132 --> 00:18:53,831
Nothing for you.
Come on, duncan.

344
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,434
I got these.
Look, I know
you're a cop now.

345
00:18:56,436 --> 00:18:57,835
Means you don't belong here.

346
00:19:04,776 --> 00:19:06,644
Hey, I got

347
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:08,179
What's on the list.

348
00:19:08,181 --> 00:19:10,515
Let me in.

349
00:19:22,529 --> 00:19:25,363
Let's go, let's go.

350
00:19:32,172 --> 00:19:33,204
Oh, yes!

351
00:19:34,641 --> 00:19:35,773
I won!

352
00:19:39,811 --> 00:19:42,346
See? People have fun,

353
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:45,183
They collect their winnings,
I skim a little off the top,

354
00:19:45,185 --> 00:19:47,552
Everybody's happy.
So what do you
need me for?

355
00:19:47,554 --> 00:19:50,855
Lot of chaos in this crummy town
since it all went to hell,

356
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:54,892
But the one thing I've heard
over and over again is,

357
00:19:54,894 --> 00:19:57,228
"that barbie is
a real badass."

358
00:19:57,230 --> 00:19:58,829
You're the main event.

359
00:19:58,831 --> 00:20:00,831
No, no, no, no, no.
I am not gonna fight.
You must've

360
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:04,302
Forgotten everything
we talked about yesterday then.

361
00:20:04,304 --> 00:20:06,537
About how you killed
peter shumway.

362
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:11,609
And how julia would hate
hearing about that.

363
00:20:13,645 --> 00:20:16,981
Besides, think of it
as a reunion because...

364
00:20:16,983 --> 00:20:19,817
You remember your opponent
victor rawlins, right?

365
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:21,652
Yeah, he gambled
his way

366
00:20:21,654 --> 00:20:24,422
Down the drain
a couple months ago. He lost

367
00:20:24,424 --> 00:20:26,924
His wife, his kids,
his whole life really.

368
00:20:26,926 --> 00:20:28,593
No, you're his bookie, okay?

369
00:20:28,595 --> 00:20:30,328
Not me.
Yeah, but you were
the one knocking

370
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,862
On his door forcing him
to pay up.

371
00:20:31,864 --> 00:20:33,598
Only this time you don't have
a gun and victor

372
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,766
Really looks ready
to even the score.

373
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:45,509
You take sugar, big jim?

374
00:20:45,511 --> 00:20:47,578
Yes, ma'am.

375
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:50,514
Sure mr. Luckland

376
00:20:50,516 --> 00:20:52,683
Doesn't, uh, mind us being here?

377
00:20:52,685 --> 00:20:54,018
Oh, no.

378
00:20:54,020 --> 00:20:56,721
Oliver's as hospitable
as they come.

379
00:20:56,723 --> 00:20:59,357
I was, uh,
under the impression...

380
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:01,692
Somebody else owned this house.

381
00:21:01,694 --> 00:21:03,694
No, I'm certain
he does.

382
00:21:03,696 --> 00:21:05,429
But he's not
here much.

383
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:07,932
He spends a lot of time out
at his other properties.

384
00:21:07,934 --> 00:21:10,868
That's why he has me
taking care of things.

385
00:21:12,304 --> 00:21:14,972
Sure is lucky to have a neighbor
like you, agatha.

386
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:28,419
That's my
daughter maxine.

387
00:21:28,421 --> 00:21:30,421
Now do me a favor
and drop that gun

388
00:21:30,423 --> 00:21:32,023
That's tucked
in the back of your belt.

389
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:38,896
Slowly.

390
00:21:38,898 --> 00:21:40,364
Okay.

391
00:21:45,037 --> 00:21:47,305
Maxine didn't learn

392
00:21:47,307 --> 00:21:51,409
To be the way she is
from her father.

393
00:21:57,683 --> 00:21:58,849
Who's ready for the main event?

394
00:22:01,521 --> 00:22:03,754
All right, all right,
well, your wait is over,

395
00:22:03,756 --> 00:22:08,392
Because here it is:
Victor rawlins versus

396
00:22:08,394 --> 00:22:12,630
Your special forces veteran
dale "barbie" barbara!

397
00:22:15,935 --> 00:22:19,003
The rules are simple:
There aren't any.

398
00:22:19,005 --> 00:22:20,805
There's no rounds,
no time limits.

399
00:22:20,807 --> 00:22:22,406
You fight till you lose.

400
00:22:23,608 --> 00:22:25,943
May the best man win.

401
00:22:28,081 --> 00:22:29,613
Disappoint me at your own risk.

402
00:23:00,712 --> 00:23:01,912
Sit.

403
00:23:01,914 --> 00:23:04,548
Make yourself
comfortable.

404
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:07,017
Maxine should be here
after sundown.

405
00:23:07,019 --> 00:23:09,019
Or maybe tomorrow.

406
00:23:09,021 --> 00:23:11,622
Well, that's a long time
to hold a rifle on someone.

407
00:23:11,624 --> 00:23:14,725
I hope I don't get drowsy,
somehow pull the trigger.

408
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:18,996
You don't remember me, do you?

409
00:23:18,998 --> 00:23:21,532
Well, give me a hint.

410
00:23:21,534 --> 00:23:26,103
We were in the same
high school class.

411
00:23:26,105 --> 00:23:27,905
Well, until I dropped out.

412
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:31,542
There's only one student
I remember dropping out.

413
00:23:32,744 --> 00:23:34,545
Her name was claire.

414
00:23:34,547 --> 00:23:37,181
I changed my name.

415
00:23:37,183 --> 00:23:39,083
I'm sure you can imagine why.

416
00:23:39,085 --> 00:23:41,886
It was quite
the scandal.

417
00:23:41,888 --> 00:23:43,053
You got pregnant.

418
00:23:43,055 --> 00:23:46,157
With maxine.

419
00:23:46,159 --> 00:23:48,726
I was only 16.

420
00:23:48,728 --> 00:23:51,629
And people treated me
like my life was
already over.

421
00:23:51,631 --> 00:23:53,097
That's not true.
I was a pariah.

422
00:23:53,099 --> 00:23:55,800
I had no way
to support my daughter...

423
00:23:56,935 --> 00:24:00,771
...Except by starting
to let men in my bed.

424
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:05,176
Men who would turn around
and publicly shame me

425
00:24:05,178 --> 00:24:07,511
For being
the immoral one.

426
00:24:07,513 --> 00:24:09,180
Still you're here.

427
00:24:09,182 --> 00:24:12,516
Far enough away
to keep the stink
out of our hair.

428
00:24:12,518 --> 00:24:13,617
Maxine moved
to westlake,

429
00:24:13,619 --> 00:24:16,086
And I came here
to be close to her.

430
00:24:16,088 --> 00:24:21,792
But neither of us will ever
forget the <i>real</i> chester's mill.

431
00:24:23,495 --> 00:24:27,097
The sharp teeth behind
the friendly smile.

432
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:30,134
Well, there <i>are</i> teeth
behind the smile.

433
00:24:30,136 --> 00:24:32,670
It's the only way
to get things done.

434
00:24:32,672 --> 00:24:35,072
Like the propane, you mean?

435
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:40,110
My daughter tells me
everything.

436
00:24:40,112 --> 00:24:44,114
Gave me every bit of evidence
I need on you and duke,

437
00:24:44,116 --> 00:24:48,118
That nutty
reverend coggins.

438
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:50,754
So...

439
00:24:50,756 --> 00:24:53,724
She must have told you
about barbie, too, huh?

440
00:24:53,726 --> 00:24:55,125
Oh, yeah.

441
00:24:55,127 --> 00:24:56,694
About him breaking legs.

442
00:24:56,696 --> 00:24:58,662
Killing that dr. Shumway.

443
00:24:58,664 --> 00:25:01,699
It's no surprise
he got stuck here.

444
00:25:01,701 --> 00:25:03,601
This town...

445
00:25:03,603 --> 00:25:07,104
It always has been a magnet
for the worst of humanity...

446
00:25:07,106 --> 00:25:10,207
Like your son.

447
00:25:10,209 --> 00:25:12,710
Junior's turning out

448
00:25:12,712 --> 00:25:14,945
To be just as crazy as his mama,
isn't he?

449
00:25:14,947 --> 00:25:17,147
Shut your mouth!
Sit down!

450
00:25:17,149 --> 00:25:19,550
Or I'll put a bullet
through your chest!

451
00:25:19,552 --> 00:25:21,619
Have you ever killed someone,
agatha?

452
00:25:21,621 --> 00:25:24,755
I mean, I know you got
your sob story and all,
but have you ever

453
00:25:24,757 --> 00:25:26,924
Really rolled up your sleeves
and murdered someone?

454
00:25:26,926 --> 00:25:28,292
Stop.

455
00:25:28,294 --> 00:25:32,229
And even with all that
hate in your eyes,

456
00:25:32,231 --> 00:25:34,732
I'm not seeing what
it takes to kill.

457
00:25:34,734 --> 00:25:37,268
But go ahead...

458
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:39,737
Prove me wrong.

459
00:25:45,610 --> 00:25:47,711
Now we're gonna do something
about <i>your</i> family.

460
00:25:49,147 --> 00:25:53,017
So this place belonged
to junior's mother?

461
00:25:53,019 --> 00:25:55,819
Yeah. He brought me
here yesterday...

462
00:25:55,821 --> 00:25:59,123
To show me this.

463
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,928
Pink stars.

464
00:26:03,930 --> 00:26:06,063
This and the fact
that he's had seizures?

465
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:08,165
I'm still gonna kill him.

466
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:12,269
No, joe, it doesn't matter
what we want.

467
00:26:12,271 --> 00:26:15,773
It matters what the dome wants.

468
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:19,310
Now we just need
to find junior.

469
00:26:19,312 --> 00:26:21,278
I'm right here.

470
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,080
What the hell
are you doing with that?

471
00:26:23,082 --> 00:26:24,248
You son of a bitch!

472
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:25,082
Angie
joe! No!

473
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:27,718
No-no-no-no!
Joe, no!

474
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:29,086
Stop!
Junior:
You're attacking me?

475
00:26:29,088 --> 00:26:31,021
You're the one
who's trespassing.

476
00:26:31,023 --> 00:26:32,256
You kidnapped
my sister!

477
00:26:32,258 --> 00:26:33,891
Junior!
You promised my dad

478
00:26:33,893 --> 00:26:35,326
You wouldn't tell
anyone about that.

479
00:26:35,328 --> 00:26:37,328
I had to!
Just like you have

480
00:26:37,330 --> 00:26:39,096
To help us now!
What?

481
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:42,299
Look, first let him go!
Let him go! Let him go!

482
00:26:42,301 --> 00:26:43,634
Junior, no!
Let him...!

483
00:26:46,939 --> 00:26:48,639
Why should I help you
with anything?

484
00:26:48,641 --> 00:26:50,608
I brought you here

485
00:26:50,610 --> 00:26:52,242
Because I trusted you.

486
00:26:52,244 --> 00:26:57,781
These are the only things
I have left of my mother.

487
00:26:57,783 --> 00:27:00,084
Junior, you said
yesterday

488
00:27:00,086 --> 00:27:02,686
That something bigger
is going on, right?

489
00:27:02,688 --> 00:27:04,755
Something that connects
all of us to what's happening?

490
00:27:04,757 --> 00:27:06,290
Yeah. So?

491
00:27:06,292 --> 00:27:09,860
So I need you to come with us
to our barn.

492
00:27:11,262 --> 00:27:12,363
Why?

493
00:27:12,365 --> 00:27:13,230
Because...

494
00:27:13,232 --> 00:27:15,299
All of us...

495
00:27:17,235 --> 00:27:20,304
...The four of us--
are connected

496
00:27:20,306 --> 00:27:23,007
To something...

497
00:27:23,009 --> 00:27:24,742
Amazing.

498
00:27:35,286 --> 00:27:36,854
Get out there!

499
00:27:56,808 --> 00:27:59,309
Woman:
Come on, barbie! Whoo!

500
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:02,880
Man:
Finish it!

501
00:28:02,882 --> 00:28:04,248
Man 2:
Loser!

502
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:07,384
Finish it!

503
00:28:07,386 --> 00:28:09,353
Stay down, you bum!
Stay down!

504
00:28:09,355 --> 00:28:11,789
Stay down!
You're out! Stay down!

505
00:28:11,791 --> 00:28:13,057
Get up.

506
00:28:13,059 --> 00:28:16,427
Hey, big man. Hey!

507
00:28:16,429 --> 00:28:19,129
No wonder your wife and kids
left you.

508
00:28:22,434 --> 00:28:25,302
Hit me as hard
as you can.

509
00:28:34,312 --> 00:28:36,847
man:
Get up!

510
00:28:42,020 --> 00:28:44,021
Woman:
Come on, barbie! Seriously?!

511
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:49,460
Let's go!
Get back up!

512
00:29:11,316 --> 00:29:14,017
I guess the best man won.

513
00:29:15,488 --> 00:29:17,988
You threw the fight
just like I knew you would.

514
00:29:17,990 --> 00:29:19,323
Oh, like hell I did.

515
00:29:19,325 --> 00:29:21,225
Everyone here bet
on the hero

516
00:29:21,227 --> 00:29:22,359
And lost their asses.

517
00:29:22,361 --> 00:29:23,460
I bet on victor...

518
00:29:23,462 --> 00:29:26,897
Because I know you.

519
00:29:26,899 --> 00:29:31,535
And I know that you would do
anything except let me win.

520
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:41,378
Here it is, duke's
safe-deposit box.

521
00:29:47,085 --> 00:29:49,019
Oh, my god.

522
00:29:49,954 --> 00:29:51,121
What is that?

523
00:29:51,123 --> 00:29:54,158
When duke woke up
from his heart surgery

524
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,126
When he had his
pacemaker put in,

525
00:29:56,128 --> 00:29:59,363
I gave him this.

526
00:30:00,499 --> 00:30:02,566
I told him the doctors found it

527
00:30:02,568 --> 00:30:05,469
Where his heart
should have been.

528
00:30:05,471 --> 00:30:08,839
I can't believe he kept it.

529
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:12,843
There's a letter here.

530
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,280
I can't.

531
00:30:16,282 --> 00:30:17,981
You read it.

532
00:30:20,952 --> 00:30:24,288
"to whom it may concern,

533
00:30:24,290 --> 00:30:27,157
"my name is duke perkins,
sheriff of chester's mill,

534
00:30:27,159 --> 00:30:29,493
"the only place I've ever been
able to call home.

535
00:30:29,495 --> 00:30:32,830
That's the reason I did
what I did."

536
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,000
His confession.

537
00:30:37,002 --> 00:30:40,537
"19 years ago
I lost my son to drugs.

538
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:44,575
I watched helplessly
as he was swept away
by his addiction."

539
00:30:44,577 --> 00:30:45,576
Did you know this?

540
00:30:45,578 --> 00:30:47,077
He never talked about it.

541
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:48,445
"the only thing
that kept me

542
00:30:48,447 --> 00:30:52,382
"from turning my gun
on myself was a promise I made:

543
00:30:52,384 --> 00:30:54,051
"to do everything I could

544
00:30:54,053 --> 00:30:56,119
"to keep drugs out
of chester's mill.

545
00:30:56,121 --> 00:30:58,155
"so I made a deal
with a devil

546
00:30:58,157 --> 00:30:59,923
By the name of
maxine seagrave."

547
00:30:59,925 --> 00:31:01,992
That's got to be the woman
in the video.

548
00:31:01,994 --> 00:31:03,927
"the deal was simple:
The town bought

549
00:31:03,929 --> 00:31:05,495
"the liquid propane
she needed

550
00:31:05,497 --> 00:31:07,464
"under the guise
of 'emergency reserves'

551
00:31:07,466 --> 00:31:09,399
"so the dea
wouldn't look into it,

552
00:31:09,401 --> 00:31:13,036
"and she'd pay us enough
to shore up the town's coffers

553
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:15,405
"and keep her drugs--
all drugs--

554
00:31:15,407 --> 00:31:18,141
Out of chester's mill."

555
00:31:20,278 --> 00:31:21,645
He did it to save us.

556
00:31:21,647 --> 00:31:24,414
"I sold my soul
for the people of this town.

557
00:31:24,416 --> 00:31:27,551
"people like my son.

558
00:31:27,553 --> 00:31:30,153
"people like linda esquivel.

559
00:31:30,155 --> 00:31:33,323
"there were two other people
in this deal:

560
00:31:33,325 --> 00:31:38,629
"lester coggins...
Who laundered our proceeds,

561
00:31:38,631 --> 00:31:40,964
"and the man who was the front,

562
00:31:40,966 --> 00:31:45,903
"saying he was buying
the propane for our town:

563
00:31:45,905 --> 00:31:47,638
Big jim rennie."

564
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:52,376
Of course he was involved.

565
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:57,681
why didn't duke tell me?

566
00:31:58,650 --> 00:32:00,484
Because he loved you.

567
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:06,290
Maybe the same reason
peter didn't tell me.

568
00:32:09,027 --> 00:32:11,595
You think you could hold
a flashlight for me?

569
00:32:33,051 --> 00:32:36,653
I need to talk to barbie.

570
00:32:41,592 --> 00:32:44,461
So,

571
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:46,563
What are you planning
on doing with me?

572
00:32:46,565 --> 00:32:49,499
My experience has been
that with a little patience,

573
00:32:49,501 --> 00:32:53,003
The world reveals
the right course of action.

574
00:32:53,005 --> 00:32:57,107
You think the world is just
looking out for you, don't you?

575
00:32:57,109 --> 00:33:00,010
As if whoever and whatever
is behind that curtain

576
00:33:00,012 --> 00:33:02,479
Is pulling strings
just for you.

577
00:33:02,481 --> 00:33:04,614
There's nothing
behind that curtain

578
00:33:04,616 --> 00:33:06,416
But darkness.
Sit down.

579
00:33:06,418 --> 00:33:08,685
Agatha!

580
00:33:12,358 --> 00:33:14,725
Hey!

581
00:33:14,727 --> 00:33:17,394
Help me!

582
00:33:26,371 --> 00:33:28,205
Please.

583
00:33:28,207 --> 00:33:29,439
Help me!

584
00:33:29,441 --> 00:33:31,141
My hands are tied.

585
00:33:31,143 --> 00:33:32,576
Help!

586
00:33:32,578 --> 00:33:34,478
Please, help me!

587
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:42,019
Help! Help!

588
00:33:49,594 --> 00:33:51,194
Cheer up, barbie.

589
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:53,563
You know the house
always wins.

590
00:34:03,408 --> 00:34:05,542
Tonight was rather successful,
wasn't it?

591
00:34:05,544 --> 00:34:07,344
I won.

592
00:34:07,346 --> 00:34:10,480
You... Helped me win.

593
00:34:13,084 --> 00:34:14,451
I've always known--

594
00:34:14,453 --> 00:34:16,053
And I think
you have, too--

595
00:34:16,055 --> 00:34:17,721
That we make
a damn good team.

596
00:34:17,723 --> 00:34:19,456
And as long as this dome
is around,

597
00:34:19,458 --> 00:34:21,525
I could see us making this town
our playground.

598
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:32,202
These people aren't
gonna let you win.

599
00:34:32,204 --> 00:34:34,371
Yeah, you got a few
that owe you something now,

600
00:34:34,373 --> 00:34:35,806
But at the end of the day,

601
00:34:35,808 --> 00:34:37,407
That ain't a whole
hell of a lot.

602
00:34:37,409 --> 00:34:40,343
Yeah, until more people owe me

603
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:43,246
And then more people
on top of them.

604
00:34:43,248 --> 00:34:44,781
I'll live
the way I want, barbie.

605
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:47,818
<i>We</i> will live the way we want.

606
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:51,221
What if you don't get more?

607
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:53,356
Huh?

608
00:34:53,358 --> 00:34:56,460
You don't get your whiskey?

609
00:34:56,462 --> 00:34:59,296
You don't get me?

610
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:05,569
Then I'll burn the place down.

611
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,110
What are you doing?

612
00:35:13,112 --> 00:35:14,444
What I should've done

613
00:35:14,446 --> 00:35:17,347
Oh, you do not want
to piss me off, dale.

614
00:35:17,349 --> 00:35:18,782
Not when under your feet

615
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:20,750
Lies a body belonging
to peter shumway.

616
00:35:20,752 --> 00:35:22,452
You do everything I say

617
00:35:22,454 --> 00:35:24,855
Or the truth about
him will come out.

618
00:35:24,857 --> 00:35:28,358
That's... See, that's
the old barbie.

619
00:35:31,195 --> 00:35:33,630
We're finished, max.

620
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:51,548
Didn't expect
to see you here.

621
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:54,417
I didn't expect to be here.

622
00:35:57,355 --> 00:35:59,456
You and I need to talk.

623
00:35:59,458 --> 00:36:01,558
Sure.

624
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,393
Come on in.

625
00:36:03,395 --> 00:36:05,695
I'll even cook us up
some dinner.

626
00:36:05,697 --> 00:36:08,265
How's something
medium-rare sound?

627
00:36:08,267 --> 00:36:10,600
Actually, let's do this
at the station.

628
00:36:18,276 --> 00:36:20,510
I've had a hell of a day, linda.

629
00:36:20,512 --> 00:36:24,281
Whatever it is you think
we need to talk about,

630
00:36:24,283 --> 00:36:26,883
It can wait till
the morning.

631
00:36:26,885 --> 00:36:29,819
Think I've, uh,

632
00:36:29,821 --> 00:36:33,623
Earned that much respect
in this town, right?

633
00:36:37,628 --> 00:36:39,796
Come by first thing,

634
00:36:39,798 --> 00:36:41,598
Or I come back

635
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:44,467
And these cuffs
don't stay on my belt.

636
00:37:04,522 --> 00:37:06,623
I need to say something.

637
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:19,703
Like why your face
is all cut up?

638
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:40,991
Look...

639
00:37:40,993 --> 00:37:44,628
I told you when I first came
to this town

640
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:48,531
That I went out to the cabin
to meet peter,

641
00:37:48,533 --> 00:37:50,600
But that...

642
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:52,302
That he wasn't there.

643
00:37:53,037 --> 00:37:55,438
But he was, wasn't he?

644
00:37:57,775 --> 00:37:59,609
Yeah.

645
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:02,746
He-he told me
that he didn't have

646
00:38:02,748 --> 00:38:05,715
The money he owed, so...

647
00:38:05,717 --> 00:38:07,784
So I said I'd be back
the next day...

648
00:38:07,786 --> 00:38:10,420
And he pulled a gun on you.

649
00:38:11,355 --> 00:38:13,690
How do you know this?

650
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:19,329
Because I brought this down
from our bedroom closet

651
00:38:19,331 --> 00:38:22,432
And found his gun missing.

652
00:38:22,434 --> 00:38:25,568
No gun, all the bullets.

653
00:38:35,746 --> 00:38:38,515
So...

654
00:38:40,686 --> 00:38:43,720
You know.

655
00:38:48,959 --> 00:38:51,094
I didn't want to believe it.

656
00:38:59,704 --> 00:39:01,604
He needed you to kill him.

657
00:39:01,606 --> 00:39:05,742
I found this life
insurance policy today.

658
00:39:11,082 --> 00:39:12,782
You know, in some weird way,

659
00:39:12,784 --> 00:39:14,851
I think he did all this
to try to protect me.

660
00:39:14,853 --> 00:39:18,822
'cause this would be void
if he committed suicide.

661
00:39:32,371 --> 00:39:34,871
I'm-I'm so sorry...

662
00:39:36,807 --> 00:39:38,742
...For everything.

663
00:39:41,545 --> 00:39:43,613
Me, too.

664
00:39:51,622 --> 00:39:54,724
Barbie, I've seen you sacrifice
yourself for total strangers.

665
00:39:59,397 --> 00:40:02,432
But in the future,
there can be no more lies.

666
00:40:04,769 --> 00:40:06,836
In the future?

667
00:40:11,675 --> 00:40:13,777
You sure?

668
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:18,782
Maybe.

669
00:40:33,697 --> 00:40:35,465
Is that...

670
00:40:35,467 --> 00:40:38,601
An egg?

671
00:40:38,603 --> 00:40:41,638
With a mini-dome
around it.

672
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:43,440
Hey, look.

673
00:40:43,442 --> 00:40:46,042
The caterpillar's
in a cocoon now.

674
00:40:46,044 --> 00:40:48,144
It's actually a chrysalis.

675
00:40:49,814 --> 00:40:52,649
He's a nerd.

676
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:13,002
And you think I'm supposed
to be part of this, too?

677
00:41:13,938 --> 00:41:15,972
Yeah.

678
00:41:15,974 --> 00:41:18,041
We do.

679
00:42:03,888 --> 00:42:05,955
Oh, my god.

680
00:42:05,957 --> 00:42:08,191
It's the pink stars.

681
00:42:09,894 --> 00:42:12,996
Joe:
And they're making
constellations.

682
00:42:20,905 --> 00:42:24,741
It's... Beautiful.

683
00:42:24,743 --> 00:42:24,774
But... What does it mean?
